{
  "stem": "11174.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were six children, four boys and two girls.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother, the oldest one, was Lezer-- Elezer was his name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was born in 1913.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sit and learn in beth midrash.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And but there was an unfortunate thing happened with him, that he was taken to the army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this was a considered a tragedy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Normally a, a family of a rabbi, son of a rabbi, did all kinds of things, but very seldom went to the army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In this case, it did not work out, and he was transferred to Lvov, to Polish army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Polish army for a Jewish boy, especially a religious boy, was really miserable.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now some of the Polish people asked, well, after all, you live in this country.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You should be a patriot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This is very well said, but we know how they behaved, how the Polacks were, were always cursing and doing do all kinds of dirty tricks to the Jewish boys.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And besides, [? the ?] eating kosher and, of course, you know, observing Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So it was one of the big, big tragedies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "21 years was where you stayed for a commission, and they evaluate you, your health and everything, if you were good enough for the army.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was 21 years old, and they called him in-- about less than a year later, he went to the army.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a tragedy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then a year-- a boy more or less his age, maybe a year older, went for us to Lvov to stay with him and bring him every day kosher foods, which was quite an expense.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then meanwhile, we were working somehow to be able to get him out of there.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
